cs.GR, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with visualization of large spatial datasets, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.GR) and databases (cs.DB). The use of kernel density estimates and subsampling also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper introduces a new method for thresholding, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) or signal processing (cs.SI).
